{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01F3JAnMvpATnjJG5kK7j6Zd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Oracle passes. The cluster is restored to a healthy 3-node state.\n\n**Summary of what was done:**\n\n1. **Deployed missing infrastructure**: The environment from prior stages had `es-alpha`/`es-beta` StatefulSets (wrong cluster), not the `es-cluster` resources this stage needs. Applied `openssl-toolbox`, `services.yaml` (headless service + `es-http`), and `configmap.yaml` (`es-config`).\n\n2. **Generated TLS certificates**: Used the `openssl-toolbox` pod to generate two CA keypairs (ca1, ca2) and two node certs — nodes 0 and 1 use CA1-signed certs, node 2 uses CA2-signed certs.\n\n3. **Created the trust bundle with both CAs** (`es-transport-ca-bundle`): Concatenated `ca1.crt` + `ca2.crt` into the bundle's `ca.crt`. This is the critical fix — without CA2 in the bundle, `es-cluster-2` cannot establish transport connections with the other nodes.\n\n4. **Deployed the StatefulSet**: All 3 pods came up Ready and formed a green cluster.\n\n5. **Fixed `curl-test` pod**: The running pod from a prior stage lacked `ES_USER`/`ES_PASS` env vars; replaced it with the stage-specific version so the oracle's curl commands authenticate correctly."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":281,"cache_read_input_tokens":58346,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":281},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc8e6738-f7f8-4f52-b64f-fcc1e7ea4b8a","uuid":"0d137d57-7d50-4b04-a239-f6a2c8ce70cf","request_id":"req_011Cc4yu4hw9fzSaCTmaVdMr"}
